#: src/glossary.md:3
msgid "Plain-language definitions of the terms and acronyms used across this documentation. It exists so a first-time or non-specialist reader can decode the security and architecture jargon without leaving the page they are on."
msgstr "以淺白語言定義本文件各處使用的術語與縮寫。它的存在，是為了讓初次接觸或非專業的讀者不必離開當前頁面，就能解讀安全與架構方面的術語。"

#: src/glossary.md:7
msgid "Product concepts"
msgstr "產品概念"

#: src/glossary.md:9
msgid "**AI Agent Assembly (AAASM)** : The product this hub documents: a governance layer that sits between your AI agents and the outside world and enforces policy, tracks cost, and intercepts unsafe actions before they run."
msgstr "**AI Agent Assembly（AAASM）** : 本中樞所記載的產品：一個位於你的 AI 代理與外部世界之間的治理層，會強制執行政策、追蹤成本，並在不安全的動作執行之前加以攔截。"

#: src/glossary.md:14
msgid "**Governance layer** : The one-line description of what AI Agent Assembly _is_ — a control that evaluates and enforces what an agent is allowed to do, rather than only observing what it did after the fact."
msgstr "**治理層** : 一句話描述 AI Agent Assembly _是_什麼 — 一種評估並強制規範代理被允許做什麼的控制機制，而非僅在事後觀察它做了什麼。"

#: src/glossary.md:19
msgid "**Gateway (`aa-gateway`)** : The central service that holds the agent registry, evaluates policy, and tracks per-team budgets. Every interception layer reports to it."
msgstr "**閘道（`aa-gateway`）** : 掌管代理註冊表、評估政策並依團隊追蹤預算的中央服務。每一層攔截都會回報給它。"

#: src/glossary.md:23
msgid "**Agent** : An autonomous or semi-autonomous program that calls tools, models, or network services on your behalf — the thing AI Agent Assembly governs."
msgstr "**代理（Agent）** : 一種代你呼叫工具、模型或網路服務的自主或半自主程式 — 也就是 AI Agent Assembly 所治理的對象。"

#: src/glossary.md:27
msgid "**Policy** : A set of allow / deny / audit rules that decide whether an agent action is permitted. See the [Policy reference](policy-reference.md)."
msgstr "**政策（Policy）** : 一組允許／拒絕／稽核規則，用以決定某個代理動作是否被許可。請參閱[政策參考](policy-reference.md)。"

#: src/glossary.md:31
msgid "**Policy-as-code** : Expressing those rules as versioned YAML/JSON documents that can be reviewed and deployed through normal Git workflows, instead of clicking through a UI."
msgstr "**政策即程式碼（Policy-as-code）** : 將這些規則表達為受版本控管的 YAML/JSON 文件，透過一般的 Git 工作流程來審查與部署，而非在 UI 上逐一點選。"

#: src/glossary.md:35
msgid "**Budget** : A per-team cap on token or dollar spend. When exceeded, the gateway can deny further agent calls."
msgstr "**預算（Budget）** : 針對每個團隊在權杖或金額開銷上的上限。一旦超過，閘道即可拒絕後續的代理呼叫。"

#: src/glossary.md:39
msgid "Interception layers"
msgstr "攔截層"

#: src/glossary.md:41
msgid "**SDK layer** : In-process governance: the language SDK wraps your agent's calls and applies allow/deny decisions before any request leaves the process."
msgstr "**SDK 層** : 行程內的治理：對應語言的 SDK 會包裝你的代理呼叫，並在任何請求離開行程之前套用允許／拒絕的決策。"

#: src/glossary.md:45
msgid "**Sidecar proxy (`aa-proxy`)** : A companion process that intercepts an agent's outbound HTTPS traffic to enforce policy without changing the agent's code."
msgstr "**邊車代理（`aa-proxy`）** : 一個伴隨執行的行程，攔截代理對外的 HTTPS 流量以強制執行政策，且無需變更代理的程式碼。"

#: src/glossary.md:49
msgid "**eBPF sensor (`aa-ebpf`)** : A kernel-level sensor (Linux only) that watches TLS libraries and process syscalls to catch actions — and bypass attempts — that the layers above miss."
msgstr "**eBPF 感測器（`aa-ebpf`）** : 一個核心層級的感測器（僅限 Linux），監看 TLS 函式庫與行程系統呼叫，以捕捉上層所遺漏的動作 — 以及繞道嘗試。"

#: src/glossary.md:53
msgid "Security & identity terms"
msgstr "安全與身分術語"

#: src/glossary.md:55
msgid "**eBPF** (extended Berkeley Packet Filter) : A Linux kernel technology for safely running small sandboxed programs inside the kernel to observe or filter events, without modifying kernel source."
msgstr "**eBPF**（extended Berkeley Packet Filter，延伸柏克萊封包過濾器） : 一種 Linux 核心技術，可在核心內安全地執行小型沙箱程式以觀察或過濾事件，而無需修改核心原始碼。"

#: src/glossary.md:59
msgid "**uprobe** (user-space probe) : An eBPF hook attached to a function in a user-space library (for example, an SSL library) so the sensor can observe calls at that point."
msgstr "**uprobe**（使用者空間探針） : 一種附掛到使用者空間函式庫（例如 SSL 函式庫）中某函式的 eBPF 掛鉤，使感測器能在該處觀察呼叫。"

#: src/glossary.md:63
msgid "**Sidecar** : A deployment pattern where a helper process runs alongside your application and handles a cross-cutting concern (here, traffic interception)."
msgstr "**邊車（Sidecar）** : 一種部署模式，讓輔助行程與你的應用程式並列執行，並處理某項橫切關注點（此處為流量攔截）。"

#: src/glossary.md:67
msgid "**MitM** (man-in-the-middle) : Sitting in the path of a connection to inspect or control it. The proxy performs _authorized_ MitM of an agent's HTTPS using a per-host certificate authority so it can apply egress policy."
msgstr "**MitM**（man-in-the-middle，中間人） : 位於連線路徑之中以檢查或控制該連線。此代理使用每主機的憑證機構，對代理的 HTTPS 執行_經授權_的 MitM，以便套用出向（egress）政策。"

#: src/glossary.md:72
msgid "**mTLS** (mutual TLS) : TLS where **both** the client and the server present certificates, so each side cryptographically verifies the other's identity."
msgstr "**mTLS**（mutual TLS，雙向 TLS） : 一種**雙方**（用戶端與伺服器）都出示憑證的 TLS，使各方以密碼學方式驗證對方的身分。"

#: src/glossary.md:76
msgid "**STRIDE** : A threat-modeling framework categorizing risks as Spoofing, Tampering, Repudiation, Information disclosure, Denial of service, and Elevation of privilege. Used in the [Security model](security-model.md)."
msgstr "**STRIDE** : 一種威脅建模框架，將風險分類為假冒（Spoofing）、竄改（Tampering）、否認（Repudiation）、資訊洩漏（Information disclosure）、阻斷服務（Denial of service）與權限提升（Elevation of privilege）。用於[安全模型](security-model.md)。"

#: src/glossary.md:81
msgid "**SCIM** (System for Cross-domain Identity Management) : A standard protocol for automatically provisioning and de-provisioning users and groups from your identity provider into an application."
msgstr "**SCIM**（System for Cross-domain Identity Management，跨網域身分管理系統） : 一種標準協定，可將使用者與群組從你的身分供應商自動佈建（provision）與解除佈建（de-provision）到某個應用程式中。"

#: src/glossary.md:85
msgid "**SSO / SAML 2.0 / OIDC** : Single sign-on and the two federation protocols (SAML 2.0 and OpenID Connect) used to let operators log in with an enterprise identity provider."
msgstr "**SSO / SAML 2.0 / OIDC** : 單一登入（Single sign-on），以及兩種聯合驗證協定（SAML 2.0 與 OpenID Connect），用以讓維運人員使用企業身分供應商登入。"

#: src/glossary.md:89
msgid "**Ed25519** : A modern public-key signature algorithm, used here to sign agent identity tokens."
msgstr "**Ed25519** : 一種現代的公開金鑰簽章演算法，此處用於簽署代理身分權杖。"

#: src/glossary.md:93
msgid "**AES-256-GCM** : A symmetric authenticated-encryption algorithm, used here to encrypt stored secrets at rest."
msgstr "**AES-256-GCM** : 一種對稱式驗證加密演算法，此處用於加密靜態儲存的機密。"

#: src/glossary.md:97
msgid "**HMAC-SHA256** : A keyed hash used to sign audit-log entries and webhook payloads so tampering is detectable."
msgstr "**HMAC-SHA256** : 一種帶金鑰的雜湊，用於簽署稽核紀錄項目與 webhook 負載，使竄改可被偵測。"

#: src/glossary.md:101
msgid "**IronClaw five-layer defense** : The name for AI Agent Assembly's defense-in-depth model — five security _layers_ (Boundary, Identity, Policy, Vault, Telemetry). These are distinct from the three _interception points_ (SDK, proxy, eBPF), which all live inside the Boundary layer. See the [Security model](security-model.md)."
msgstr "**IronClaw 五層防禦** : AI Agent Assembly 縱深防禦模型的名稱 — 五個安全_層_（Boundary、Identity、Policy、Vault、Telemetry）。這些不同於三個_攔截點_（SDK、proxy、eBPF），後者全都位於 Boundary 層之內。請參閱[安全模型](security-model.md)。"

#: src/glossary.md:107
msgid "**Audit log** : The append-only, tamper-evident record of every agent action (policy checks, events, budget debits)."
msgstr "**稽核紀錄（Audit log）** : 針對每個代理動作（政策檢查、事件、預算扣抵）的僅可附加、可察覺竄改的紀錄。"

